1
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:40,759
We're done for!

2
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:42,000
You okay?

3
00:00:45,399 --> 00:00:46,039
Lao Lian.

4
00:00:47,719 --> 00:00:49,119
Lao Lian, where are the others?

5
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:52,119
How could you leave them up there alone?

6
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:55,240
And did you find the Silver Eye?

7
00:00:55,799 --> 00:00:58,759
The Silver Eye got smashed to pieces.

8
00:00:59,079 --> 00:00:59,880
What?

9
00:01:00,159 --> 00:01:01,359
The Silver Eye is broken?

10
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:02,920
Did they do something to it?

11
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:06,079
Next time you talk behind someone's back,

12
00:01:06,359 --> 00:01:07,719
check which way the wind's blowing.

13
00:01:08,159 --> 00:01:10,840
Gossips are either crooks or thieves.

14
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:12,040
What did you say, you fat slob?

15
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:13,000
Why so worked up?

16
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:14,239
Are you the crook or the thief?

17
00:01:14,239 --> 00:01:14,959
All right, all right.

18
00:01:14,959 --> 00:01:17,200
Well, if it's broken, it's broken.

19
00:01:17,560 --> 00:01:19,159
As long as everyone's safe.

20
00:01:19,359 --> 00:01:21,159
The Silver Eye map was pieced together.

21
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:22,400
I still remember some of it.

22
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:26,719
Ms. He, are you saying

23
00:01:27,079 --> 00:01:28,719
you can recreate it?

24
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:31,640
I'll give it a try.

25
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:33,719
That would be wonderful.

26
00:01:33,719 --> 00:01:35,439
Ms. He, do you know how crucial

27
00:01:35,439 --> 00:01:37,519
the Silver Eye is to this whole trip?

28
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:40,200
Acting like a lapdog.

29
00:01:40,760 --> 00:01:41,400
Old Chen.

30
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:43,879
The fog should be rolling in by now.

31
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:45,000
Let's set up camp.

32
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:46,239
Okay.

33
00:01:46,439 --> 00:01:47,439
If you're so good, you do it.

34
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:49,599
I'm just here to supervise you.

35
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:51,079
Hurry up. Look at the state of you.

36
00:01:52,719 --> 00:01:53,959
Eat, eat.

37
00:01:53,959 --> 00:01:54,760
Thanks.

38
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:56,640
Let me tell you,

39
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:57,840
just now,

40
00:01:57,840 --> 00:02:00,400
I saw that statue down there.

41
00:02:00,719 --> 00:02:02,120
It's incredible.

42
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,959
That's a real treasure.

43
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:06,280
Absolutely priceless.

44
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:08,840
That craftsmanship... forget the past,

45
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,560
even today,

46
00:02:10,599 --> 00:02:12,000
no one could replicate it.

47
00:02:13,719 --> 00:02:15,520
I checked the map carefully.

48
00:02:15,719 --> 00:02:16,960
To get to Mengna Valley,

49
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:19,120
the Nine-Story Pagoda is the only way.

50
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:20,560
Does it say anywhere

51
00:02:21,039 --> 00:02:21,520
um,

52
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:24,240
which way the city of Mengna Valley is?

53
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:26,280
The whole Mengna Valley

54
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,759
is in a place called Qingluan Sacred Hall.

55
00:02:28,919 --> 00:02:31,479
The Nine-Story Pagoda is there too.

56
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:35,199
Right, right, right.

57
00:02:35,479 --> 00:02:36,639
I remember now.

58
00:02:37,159 --> 00:02:39,520
This scroll of mine mentions it.

59
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:42,960
Four snow peaks surround Mengna Valley.

60
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,960
The four snow mountains represent

61
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:46,479
one of the four guardian deities.

62
00:02:46,759 --> 00:02:47,879
The four guardians are

63
00:02:47,879 --> 00:02:50,520
gold, silver, crystal, and glaze.

64
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:52,400
Built from these four kinds of gems.

65
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:54,639
The whole range linked together

66
00:02:54,639 --> 00:02:56,400
is called the Qingluan Sacred Hall.

67
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,639
In local legend,

68
00:02:59,719 --> 00:03:01,159
the Kunlun Mountains,

69
00:03:01,319 --> 00:03:03,280
Kunlun is known as the Land of Qingluan.

70
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,000
If

71
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:08,039
Kunlun's shape resembles a Qingluan,

72
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:10,599
then it matches that epic poem.

73
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:13,120
Per the poem, Qingluan Sacred Hall

74
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:15,759
should be in the Kunlun Range,

75
00:03:15,759 --> 00:03:16,919
at Xiaduo Yuzhang Pass.

76
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,159
Xiaduo Yuzhang Mountain

77
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:21,680
has two statues, white and silver.

78
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,360
White is the snow mountain,

79
00:03:24,599 --> 00:03:26,599
and the glacier must be the silver.

80
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:28,639
The general direction is settled.

81
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:30,680
The area is at Xiaduo Yuzhang Pass.

82
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:32,280
Plus we've got Dawang with us.

83
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,159
We'll definitely find it.

84
00:03:35,319 --> 00:03:36,039
Great.

85
00:03:48,039 --> 00:03:48,759
Let's go.

86
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,759
You mean A-Zhong

87
00:03:50,879 --> 00:03:53,360
wants to go back and steal that statue?

88
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,639
He doesn't have that kind of eye.

89
00:03:55,599 --> 00:03:56,360
But you and Old Lu

90
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,439
hyped that thing up in broad daylight

91
00:03:57,439 --> 00:03:59,039
like it was the greatest treasure ever.

92
00:03:59,039 --> 00:04:00,199
He's definitely tempted now.

93
00:04:12,599 --> 00:04:14,159
What are those two up to?

94
00:04:14,159 --> 00:04:16,279
Old Whitehair and Uncle Min's wife.

95
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,199
What are they saying?

96
00:04:19,199 --> 00:04:20,319
Let me listen, let me listen.

97
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,399
Just do as I say.

98
00:04:24,959 --> 00:04:26,160
Once this job is done,

99
00:04:26,199 --> 00:04:27,720
whether he's dead or alive,

100
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:28,839
I'll go with you.

101
00:04:28,839 --> 00:04:31,360
Sounds like these two are saying

102
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,480
once this job's done,

103
00:04:32,879 --> 00:04:34,720
they're gonna dump old Uncle Min.

104
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:36,560
That's cold.

105
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,199
No wonder I said they're rotten.

106
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:40,360
What kind of people are these?

107
00:04:40,759 --> 00:04:42,279
We've lost him! Hurry, faster!

108
00:04:42,839 --> 00:04:43,959
When we catch A-Zhong later,

109
00:04:44,319 --> 00:04:45,600
we've gotta scare him good.

110
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:46,720
Scare him however you want.

111
00:04:47,199 --> 00:04:48,199
Get ahead of him.

112
00:04:48,279 --> 00:04:49,199
How do we get ahead?

113
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:50,680
Hurry, take the shortcut.

114
00:05:03,519 --> 00:05:05,240
Commander Chen, what's the plan?

115
00:05:05,839 --> 00:05:07,560
No plan. Just charge in.

116
00:05:07,759 --> 00:05:09,199
We can't let him get into that cave.

117
00:05:09,519 --> 00:05:10,720
Right, let's go.

118
00:05:26,079 --> 00:05:27,959
Tell me, where is Dawang?

119
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:29,319
Dawang?

120
00:05:29,959 --> 00:05:30,920
You've got the wrong guy.

121
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:33,680
I'll give you one more chance.

122
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:35,560
Where is Dawang?

123
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:39,560
What do you want?

124
00:05:40,959 --> 00:05:42,240
You think if you kill me,

125
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:44,240
you can find Mengna Valley on your own?

126
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:45,959
Kill you? I wouldn't dare.

127
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,240
But making you suffer a bit,

128
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,079
that's easy enough.

129
00:06:05,079 --> 00:06:05,759
Boss.

130
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:08,079
Old Fei's been in there a while. Nothing.

131
00:06:08,199 --> 00:06:09,199
Should we go take a look?

132
00:06:10,839 --> 00:06:11,519
Let's go.

133
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:12,240
Move.

134
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:12,879
Right.

135
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,319
Stop!

136
00:06:30,839 --> 00:06:32,480
Don't run! Kill him!

137
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,399
Grab him!

138
00:06:35,199 --> 00:06:35,720
Get him!

139
00:06:36,879 --> 00:06:38,240
They're all here for Dawang.

140
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,000
Keep quiet for now.

141
00:07:10,839 --> 00:07:11,439
What is this?

142
00:07:11,439 --> 00:07:12,319
No idea.

143
00:07:14,279 --> 00:07:15,360
How come every single pillar

144
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,680
seems to be hiding something?

145
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:17,480
What is it?

146
00:07:17,519 --> 00:07:18,439
How would I know?

147
00:07:24,879 --> 00:07:25,839
A mask!

148
00:07:38,879 --> 00:07:39,639
Help!

149
00:07:40,839 --> 00:07:41,560
Help!

150
00:07:49,399 --> 00:07:50,120
Don't shoot!

151
00:07:57,199 --> 00:07:57,879
Run!

152
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:03,759
Hurry, faster!

153
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:07,000
Hurry!

154
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:09,279
This way!

155
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:10,279
Here, here, here!

156
00:08:11,079 --> 00:08:11,720
Hurry!

157
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:16,040
Hurry, hurry!

158
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:19,439
Fatty!

159
00:08:23,279 --> 00:08:25,600
Help, A-Zhong! Help me!

160
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:41,039
Move it!

161
00:08:41,279 --> 00:08:41,759
Move!

162
00:08:41,879 --> 00:08:42,759
I can't run.

163
00:08:46,519 --> 00:08:47,320
Wait for me!

164
00:08:48,799 --> 00:08:49,320
I can't.

165
00:08:49,759 --> 00:08:51,080
I've got altitude sickness!

166
00:08:51,679 --> 00:08:52,639
I can't run anymore.

167
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,120
I've been watching for a while.

168
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:59,399
They won't catch up anytime soon.

169
00:08:59,679 --> 00:09:00,480
Let's take a break.

170
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:01,240
Rest a bit.

171
00:10:01,159 --> 00:10:02,559
Run!

172
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:08,679
No, no, no!

173
00:10:08,679 --> 00:10:09,320
Hurry!

174
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,120
Hurry!

175
00:10:12,399 --> 00:10:14,120
Wait, there's no way through here!

176
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:15,279
This way, this way!

177
00:10:15,399 --> 00:10:16,039
Go!

178
00:10:17,039 --> 00:10:17,399
Fatty!

179
00:10:17,399 --> 00:10:18,159
No, no, no!

180
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:19,759
What is this?

181
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:22,000
Go, go, go!

182
00:10:32,639 --> 00:10:33,320
What do we do?

183
00:10:33,759 --> 00:10:34,480
Jump from here!

184
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,279
Jump!

185
00:10:36,639 --> 00:10:38,360
Jump, jump!

186
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:41,840
Down!

187
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:03,039
Our lifelong reputation, you and me,

188
00:11:03,039 --> 00:11:04,799
isn't gonna end right here, is it?

189
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:06,960
I-I don't wanna die here.

190
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,440
Like you have a choice?

191
00:11:08,559 --> 00:11:10,000
What... what do we do about it?

192
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,000
Grab a rock.

193
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:12,320
Hit it!

194
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:13,039
Rocks!

195
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,000
Shutong!

196
00:11:32,519 --> 00:11:33,279
Officer He!

197
00:11:33,279 --> 00:11:34,000
Shutong!

198
00:11:42,279 --> 00:11:43,080
Hurry, hurry!

199
00:12:03,559 --> 00:12:04,440
Are you okay?

200
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:07,039
Old Chen, you all right?

201
00:12:07,639 --> 00:12:08,320
I'm fine.

202
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:13,799
Dawang!

203
00:12:15,679 --> 00:12:16,480
Nobody move!

204
00:12:17,519 --> 00:12:19,440
Old Fei, tonight

205
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:21,279
you've lost quite a few men too.

206
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:23,120
All just to kill me?

207
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,519
Is it worth it?

208
00:12:24,559 --> 00:12:26,639
Yeah, is it worth it?

209
00:12:26,679 --> 00:12:28,039
But it's worth it.

210
00:12:28,919 --> 00:12:29,639
Don't move!

211
00:12:30,159 --> 00:12:32,000
Know why I have to kill him?

212
00:12:32,399 --> 00:12:33,799
He... Dawang,

213
00:12:33,799 --> 00:12:35,519
the backbone of the anti-poachers.

214
00:12:35,519 --> 00:12:36,679
I'll kill you!

215
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:47,279
Hey, Brother Chen,

216
00:12:47,799 --> 00:12:50,039
didn't I show up right on time?

217
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:53,639
Uncle Min, you showing up here now

218
00:12:54,399 --> 00:12:55,159
is just perfect.

219
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,519
I just wanna know,

220
00:12:57,879 --> 00:13:00,039
what that monster actually looks like.

221
00:13:00,039 --> 00:13:01,639
Like a giant monkey.

222
00:13:01,919 --> 00:13:03,000
A giant monkey?

223
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,120
A monkey.

224
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,440
Right, a monkey, you see,

225
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:09,559
the people living in the Himalayas,

226
00:13:09,559 --> 00:13:10,519
they believe in a kind

227
00:13:10,519 --> 00:13:12,559
of giant beast called the snow ape.

228
00:13:12,559 --> 00:13:14,240
The first to spot a snow ape's trail

229
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:16,320
was a 19th-century foreign officer.

230
00:13:16,559 --> 00:13:18,360
While climbing a snow mountain

231
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:20,279
in the northeast Himalayas,

232
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:22,320
at an altitude over 5,000 meters,

233
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:24,200
he found a snow ape's footprint.

234
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:26,679
But these snow apes live in conditions

235
00:13:26,679 --> 00:13:27,759
that are extremely harsh.

236
00:13:27,759 --> 00:13:29,519
So nobody's ever seen them.

237
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:31,080
Only in recent years,

238
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:33,480
I heard someone at the mountain's base

239
00:13:33,519 --> 00:13:34,960
discovered enormous footprints,

240
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:37,320
possibly left by these snow apes.

241
00:13:37,799 --> 00:13:38,879
You three,

242
00:13:39,039 --> 00:13:41,080
why did you go to the ruins?

243
00:13:42,679 --> 00:13:43,480
We...

244
00:13:44,639 --> 00:13:45,879
We followed A-Zhong over there.

245
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:48,000
Why would A-Zhong go to the ruins?

246
00:13:48,799 --> 00:13:50,120
Why would A-Zhong go to the ruins?

247
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,600
You think it's right to ask us that?

248
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:52,320
Go ask him yourself!

249
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:55,240
Did A-Zhong die up at the ruins?

250
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:56,240
Yeah.

251
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:57,759
How did he die?

252
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:02,919
Probably trampled to death.

253
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:04,720
Really?

254
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:07,759
Maybe you three had a fight up there

255
00:14:07,759 --> 00:14:09,039
and he got silenced?

256
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:12,600
What kind of twisted mind do you have?

257
00:14:13,039 --> 00:14:13,559
During the day,

258
00:14:13,559 --> 00:14:15,440
we mentioned that in Rahu Hall's cave,

259
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:16,799
we found a statue.

260
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:19,480
He must've set his sights on that statue.

261
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:20,399
By the time we got there,

262
00:14:20,399 --> 00:14:21,559
before we could stop him,

263
00:14:21,679 --> 00:14:22,960
the poachers arrived.

264
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,559
They clashed with A-Zhong,

265
00:14:25,159 --> 00:14:26,519
so they attracted the great ape.

266
00:14:27,799 --> 00:14:29,080
This A-Zhong, honestly,

267
00:14:29,519 --> 00:14:30,679
greedy for petty gains.

268
00:14:30,679 --> 00:14:31,320
All right,

269
00:14:31,919 --> 00:14:32,879
let's not bring this up

270
00:14:33,639 --> 00:14:34,639
again.

271
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:37,080
I trust Brother Chen.

272
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:41,759
Boss, help me!

273
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:43,480
A-Zhong!

274
00:14:46,039 --> 00:14:46,840
A-Zhong!

275
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:50,720
Didn't you say A-Zhong was trampled?

276
00:14:50,799 --> 00:14:52,519
Isn't it good news he's still alive?

277
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:59,320
Boss, I almost didn't make it back.

278
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,519
This is karma.

279
00:15:02,159 --> 00:15:04,320
He got greedy for money first,

280
00:15:04,679 --> 00:15:06,159
that's why he ended up like this.

281
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,279
If we keep bringing him along,

282
00:15:08,399 --> 00:15:10,279
it might slow down our journey.

283
00:15:10,279 --> 00:15:12,240
Boss, don't listen to her!

284
00:15:12,559 --> 00:15:14,000
They... they...

285
00:15:43,559 --> 00:15:44,279
Boss.

286
00:15:45,039 --> 00:15:46,720
I think Madam has a point.

287
00:15:48,159 --> 00:15:49,720
A-Zhong is a burden.

